---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Privacy Policy - Toolkify"
  description="Privacy Guarantee: Toolkify runs 100% in your local browser sandbox. No user inputs, JSON logs, or sketch codes are ever sent to a server."
>
  <section class="max-w-[800px] w-full mx-auto px-4 py-12 flex flex-col gap-8 animate-fade-in-up">
    <!-- Breadcrumb & Header -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold text-slate uppercase">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span class="text-brand-blue">Privacy Policy</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-display font-medium text-4xl tracking-tight text-primary mt-1">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xs text-slate">Last updated: July 5, 2026</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Core Principle Highlight -->
    <div class="p-6 bg-success-accent/5 border border-success-accent/20 rounded-2xl flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 items-start">
      <div class="text-2xl pt-0.5 select-none">🔒</div>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-base text-primary">Our Promise: Your tool data stays in your browser.</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-slate leading-relaxed">
          Toolkify is completely serverless. Every single calculator, converter, drawing canvas, and utility on this site runs directly on your machine. Your input data is never sent to our servers or third parties. However, to keep the site free, we display third-party advertisements which may collect standard browsing data (like your IP address or cookies) as detailed in Section 4 below.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Content Sections -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-8 text-sm text-slate leading-relaxed font-sans">
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary">1. Data We Do Not Collect</h3>
        <p>
          Whether you are calculating a paycheck, formatting a coding file, checking your sleep cycle, or generating passwords, we maintain zero visibility into your activities:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2 mt-1">
          <li><strong>Zero Transmissions:</strong> Your inputs and calculation results remain strictly within your browser's private sandbox thread. They are never transmitted to our servers or any third parties.</li>
          <li><strong>No Server Logs:</strong> Because these tools run without checking in with a backend API, we keep no records of what you type, calculate, or convert.</li>
          <li><strong>No Session Recording:</strong> We do not use screen-recording tools, keystroke loggers, or heatmaps to analyze your usage.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary">2. How We Use Browser Storage (`localStorage`)</h3>
        <p>
          To make your experience seamless, Toolkify stores a few minor settings directly on your device. This is saved only in your browser's local database:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2 mt-1">
          <li><strong>Your Custom Whiteboards:</strong> Your draggable notes, sketches, and canvases are saved to your local storage so they are still there when you reload the tab.</li>
          <li><strong>Site Preferences:</strong> We remember your preference for light or dark mode.</li>
          <li><strong>Quick History:</strong> We keep track of the last four tools you opened so you can jump back to them quickly from the home page.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2">
          This data is private to your device. You can clear it completely at any time by clearing your browser's history and cookies, or by resetting site data.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary">3. Email & Feedback</h3>
        <p>
          When you want to request a new tool, leave a rating, or get in touch:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2 mt-1">
          <li>We don't use server-based forms that harvest database entries. Instead, clicking contact or review links will draft an email in your own email app, which you can choose to send.</li>
          <li>If you email us, we only use your email address to reply to you or to publish your feedback (always with your explicit permission). We never sell or share your contact details.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary">4. Cookies and Advertising</h3>
        <p>
          To keep Toolkify free and accessible, this site may display advertisements served by Google AdSense and/or other third-party ad networks. When ads are shown, here is how advertising data is handled:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2 mt-1">
          <li><strong>Google AdSense & Cookies:</strong> Google uses cookies, device/browser identifiers, and standard network request data (such as your IP address) to serve ads based on your visits to Toolkify and other sites on the internet.</li>
          <li><strong>Data Processing:</strong> This data processing is managed entirely by Google, not Toolkify. You can learn more about how Google uses data by visiting <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brand-blue hover:underline">Google’s Advertising Privacy & Terms</a>.</li>
          <li><strong>Opt-Out Options:</strong> You can opt out of personalized advertising by visiting Google's <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brand-blue hover:underline">Ads Settings</a>. Alternatively, you can opt out of third-party vendors' use of cookies for personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://optout.aboutads.info" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brand-blue hover:underline">YourAdChoices</a> or <a href="https://optout.networkadvertising.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brand-blue hover:underline">Network Advertising Initiative (NAI)</a>.</li>
          <li><strong>Regional Regulations (EU, UK, California):</strong> If you access this site from regions with specific privacy laws (such as the European Union, United Kingdom, or California), you may be presented with a consent banner allowing you to customize your preferences. If you decline consent or choose not to receive personalized ads, you will only see non-personalized ads (which rely on contextual information rather than tracking profiles).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary">5. Code Auditing & Transparency</h3>
        <p>
          Since all operations happen on your screen, you can inspect the code behind any tool directly in your browser. We compile the site with standard precautions to ensure input fields are safe from cross-site scripting (XSS) and other browser-based vulnerabilities.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 border-t border-hairline pt-6">
        <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary">Questions?</h3>
        <p>
          If you have questions about our offline architecture, we'd love to chat. You can learn more on our <a href="/about" class="text-brand-blue hover:underline">About Page</a> or contact us directly on the <a href="/contact" class="text-brand-blue hover:underline">Contact Page</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
